<item>
            <title>[LU-14141] WBC: Stripe directory not flushed to MDT when it grows large enough</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14141</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently Lustre supports restriping on MDT when a directory is growing big enough.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Under WBC, in the original design, all sub files under the root WBC directory are located on the target MDT same as the root WBC directory.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To obtain the performance improvement in the DNE environment, it can also stripe the directory under WBC that not flushed to MDT when it is growing large enough.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The WBC striping can trigger only on the client side without communications with MDTs expect that get the FID seq from FLD server.&lt;br/&gt;
It only needs to determine which MDT targets the large directory will stripe into, can delay the striped directory creation until the flush time.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
